{
  "texts": [
    "A data transfer is produced for each element in the large input matrix in their implementations.",
    "For instance, each data transfer step (DPU-CPU, CPU-DPU, Inter-DPU) of NW involves more than 650000 operations of 160 Bytes on average.",
    "In the CPU-DPU step of the TRNS, more than 980000 write-to-rank operations are performed in the 480 DPU configuration of 512 bytes on average.",
    "This considerable number of data transfers significantly strains the request handling of the PIM devices, leading to high overheads.",
    "Despite the substantial overhead in these applications shown in Fig. 8, it is important to note that this represents an already optimized scenario within the vPIM system."
  ]
}